New stuff in v1.01:

GP SDK version tags — dumps every GP$xxx library string with its description and offset
Nucleus/ThreadX RTOS scan — Generalplus chips often use Nucleus RTOS, checks for those signatures
AES key hunt — hexdumps 128 bytes before + 256 after AESCipheredFile, then scans ±512 bytes for 128/192/256-bit key candidates based on entropy
NAND layout — dumps the GPNandTag/GPNandTag2 context which should show the partition table
Embedded filenames — finds .bin, .kpa, .wav, .bmp etc filenames baked into the firmware
LDR PC jump table decode — actually resolves where each ARM exception handler lives in memory
Ghidra bootstrap script — auto-generates a .java script you can run in Ghidra to label the vector table and known strings instantly
